.head 3 +  Function: DateTimeToStrYYMMDD ! __Exported
.head 4 -  Description:
.head 4 +  Returns
.head 5 -  String:
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Date/Time: dtDateTime
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  String: sYear
.head 5 -  String: sMonth
.head 5 -  String: sDay
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 -  Set sYear = SalStrRightX( SalNumberToStrX( SalDateYear( dtDateTime ), 2 ), 0 )
.head 5 -  Call StringStartPad( sYear, '0', 2 )
.head 5 -  Set sMonth = SalNumberToStrX( SalDateMonth( dtDateTime ), 0 )
.head 5 -  Call StringStartPad( sMonth, '0', 2 )
.head 5 -  Set sDay = SalNumberToStrX( SalDateDay( dtDateTime ), 0 )
.head 5 -  Call StringStartPad( sDay, '0', 2 )
.head 5 -  Return sYear || sMonth || sDay
.head 3 +  Function: DTArrayFind ! __Exported
.head 4 -  Description:
.head 4 +  Returns
.head 5 -  Boolean:
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Date/Time: dtaDateTimeArray[*]
.head 5 -  ! nArrayCount = number of elements or ARRAY_Null_Terminated constant
.head 5 -  Number: nArrayCount
.head 5 -  Date/Time: dtDateTimeToFind
.head 5 -  Receive Number: nFoundPos
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  Number: nPos
.head 5 -  Boolean: bFound
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 -  Set nFoundPos = NUMBER_Null
.head 5 -  Set nPos = 0
.head 5 -  Set bFound = FALSE
.head 5 +  If nArrayCount = ARRAY_Null_Terminated
.head 6 +  While dtaDateTimeArray[ nPos ] != DATETIME_Null AND NOT bFound
.head 7 +  If dtaDateTimeArray[ nPos ] = dtDateTimeToFind
.head 8 -  Set bFound = TRUE
.head 8 -  Set nFoundPos = nPos
.head 7 -  Set nPos = nPos + 1
.head 5 +  Else
.head 6 +  While nPos <= nArrayCount AND NOT bFound
.head 7 +  If dtaDateTimeArray[ nPos ] = dtDateTimeToFind
.head 8 -  Set bFound = TRUE
.head 8 -  Set nFoundPos = nPos
.head 7 -  Set nPos = nPos + 1
.head 5 -  Return bFound
.head 3 +  Function: MakeDateTimeList ! __Exported
.head 4 -  Description: This functions make a any character separated list into sStringList from the array dtaDT[*].
VERY IMPORTANT ASSUMPTION : dtaDT[*] is assumed to be terminated by a DATETIME_NULL value.
PARAMETERS :
  dtaDT[*] : array of DateTime stamps terminated by a DATETIME_NULL value
  sSeparator : string used as the list string separator
                       eg: jan, michelle, dani the comma is the separator
  sQuoteType : string used as the type of character for the quotes around the strings.
                         eg: "jan", "michelle", "dani" the double quote is the quote type character
                         note use sQueryType of blank to obtain a non quoted string list.
.head 4 -  Returns
